2. LazyExtras plugins
open LazyVim mode by :LazyExtras
hit x on Plugin to enable or disable it


3. third party plugins
create a new lua file in the plugins directory
write this in the  file with the string found in the installation instructions: 

return {
  "username/plugin",
  opts= {....},
  keys= {....}
}


also look in the installation instructions if an opts section needs to be added


*Installing several plugins*

return {
  {
  "username1/plugin1",
  opts= {....},
  keys= {....}
},
{
    "username2/plugin2"
    opts= {....},
    keys= {....}
  }

}
